1..    vw: viewport width ( width: 100vw; (kisi bhee device mei poora screen ka width lelega))
and if we give 80 vw it means 80% of the width le lega

2..    vh: viewport height( same like vw  bas height mei changes lelga)

3..    'em': used to multiply the size (2guna , 3 guna i.e 2em 3em)
font-size: 2em; it will make the font size 2 times 

4..    'vmin' & 'vmax': 
        device ka jo bhee minimum hoga (width or height) mei se vo humara vmin , and jo bacha vo vmax

    e.g.phone mei vmin width and vmax height
    e.g. lappi mei vmin height and vmax wid

5..  min/max height/width:  e.g. min-height: 50vh; iski height kam se kam 50 ho aur agar zyada content                          aaye toh accordingly change ho jaaye 


margin: auto; keval block level elements(div) mei hoga na ki inline elements(span)